This place is really good! Yes the service is a touch slow, but once you know that... Grab a drink and enjoy the atmosphere. Every member of the staff was so kind, it was like we were at a friends house for dinner. My hubby can be a touch picky, and they asked a few times exactly how he wanted his food to make sure it was right. He had the chicken Alfredo, which he said was great. I had a lovely glass of wine and the seafood mixture (can't remember the exact name) it was amaze balls!  We will be back... And often. So glad we found this hidden gem.

